<Author>ann99bray
<Content>Great location, value for money We stayed at the Lleo for 2 nights pre-cruise earlier this month. We took a taxi to the hotel and were allowed to check in early which was really nice. The room was fine - we were at the front of the hotel overlooking the main street which I was concerned would be noisy at night but we slept like logs. It was midweek so it may be noisier on weekends. We were also happy with the breakfast in the morning. There is a large lounge on the main floor with a computer with free internet access which I didn't realize at first. I think the Lleo offered good value because Barcelona is so expensive and a lot of hotels do not include breakfast. It was so easy to walk to Las Ramblas and the Gothic Quarter from here and there is a subway stop right across from the hotel. Metro is easy to use. We also took the Hop on, Hop off bus which leaves from Placa Catalyuna nearby. One mistake I made was to ask the front desk to call a taxi to go to the ship. It would have been less expensive to flag one down from the hotel. I should know that by now! 
