<Content>Recommend Booked hotel and flights with British Airways got a great deal. Hotel is only 5 mins walk from the top of the Ramblas - also therefore only 5 mins from Catalunya Square where you can get the metro or Bus Turistic. 2 routes available at this time of year - 26 Euros for a two day pass hop on hop off. We got into one of our two rooms prior to check in time and dumped all our luggage. The rooms were standard, clean, not very exciting - but we'd come to see Barcelona not the hotel room! We had front facing rooms which was lovely - noisey street but did not disturb sleep - noisey guests did (so take ear plugs!). Breakfast was in a very bright and cheery room - again typical breakfast, although did have English fry too! Temperature reached 76 degrees over the weekend and we LOVED the pool area at the top of the hotel. Pool is only a metre deep - but to just enjoy the blue skies, hot sun and cool water before we checked out (late check out 12noon). Hotel looked after our luggae until we returned to get a taxi. Taxi from airport including surcharges for luggage/passengers was less than 30 Euros. We just went out in the street to get a return taxi for similar amount. In general Taxis very cheap. Would recommend taxi hopping too, found these very cheap. Highlights, Sagradia Familiar (queue for the lift - if you have time!!), Port Vell, Palace and Sat night fountain display with music (8pm start I think). So much, great place. 
