<Author>WiltshireDebbie
<Content>fab location We stayed at this hotel from 2nd -6th August.We had a fantastic time!Our group consisted of 8 people -4 rooms.All of our rooms were clean and comfortable.3 rooms were on the road side and the double glazing cut out alot of the noise.Yes sometimes you could hear a siren but hey you are in the city!!We actually enjoyed sitting on the small balcony and watching the hussle and bustle!The pool on the roof terrace is small but it has jets and seats at the side which is relaxing after a day in the city.You can see alot from the roof terrace.The location of the hotel couldn't be any better. Just off La Ramba and catalonia square. Very safe to walk about at night just avoid the street cleaners at midnight washing down the paths!A gt tapas bar is celler de tapa.ask at reception for a voucher as you can get a free glass of wine.A must to do is the turistic bus - hop on hop off. two day pass is approx 22 euros.gt way to see the city.red and blue routes.We spent a day at the beach on the blue route.this can be caught just around the corner from the hotel.Reception at the hotel are really friendly and helpful.NOTE - all bars close at 11pm on sundays even the hotel bar.We did the barcelona footy stadium (on the red route) very poor but worth a visit - in your ticket price for the bus you get discount vouchers so remember to use them!Another must is the castle reached by cable car(on the blue route) approx 7 euros for cable car.fantastic views from there.we also did the art museum again fab views from outside.The olympic stadium is worth a visit too -free! you can walk to this from the art museum.*** Last point to make is beware of thiefs- one of our party had a bag pinched from beneath our noses in an ice cream palour on the last day so had his passport in -luckily easy jet let him board! take a photocopy of your passport as you never know.After checking out on your last day ask to put passports in hotel safe!! During your visit the safe in your room costs 10 euros deposit and 2.50 euros per day. ***Well i hope this is helpful.We all had a gt trip and would reccoment this hotel highly.by the way the police station is under the square!!! 
