<Author>Blondi_Baby
<Content>Great Location I stayed in the hotel Lleo in barcelona in March for 2 nights..it is a great little hotel..fine for a 3 star..the best thing about this hotel is it's location, it is located 2 minutes walk for the Plaza de Catyluna Sq.. We stayed in a room towards the back that had no view..so I would advise anyone going to put in a request for a balcony room that will overlook the street..may be a bit nosier than in the back but you will have a view over the street anyway. the breakfast in the Lleo isn't nice. the staff here were very friendly and the next time I go back to barcelona ( which i will be as it is a fabulous city)I will stay in the Lleo again bacause of it's location. If you are looking for a nice really central 4 star go for the Hotle Regina..Tip for Barcelona: Stay at least 3 nights as it is a large city and theres a lot to see..esp do trip on the Bus Turistic tours( there is a red  blue line, one is north  one is south..The north tour will take you to the Nou Camp Football stadium, and the south will take you to the zoo,olympic stadium,aquarium,beach etc..it is worth it to get the 2 day pass on this bus which cost 22 euro pp..it is a hop on hop off service that you can practically use as a taxi..Train from barcelona Airport to Plaza De Catyluna..The train station is located infront of the b terminal, when you come out of terminal B turn left ,go through a walkway bridge and down to the station here you will ask for your ticket to barcelona ( Plaza de catyluna return( it cost me 9.50 return for 2 people)..you get the train to El Prat( 1st stop) then go to Platform 2..get the train to Sants( 2 nd stop)go to platform 2, get off 1st stop for Plaza de catyluna..you will arrive at the underground stop next to the huge back overlooking the Square..next to the Banesto Bank..on your return..you have to go back down this stop next to the bank again for your journey back to the airport..go to platform2..get off in sants go to platform 5get off in El Prat.get on again at platform 3 for the airport.. it is well worth it to get the train if you are on a budget as a taxi costs around 30 euro one way...there is also a bus that goes into the Square( about 30mins of a journey 
