<Content>Recommended Good Standard The Hotel Lleo is a good base. My husband and I travelled with our four month old son. Everything we booked with the hotel (through a travel agent prior to arrival) was delivered as arranged. Breakfast very good as previous reviews have mentioned and included hot and cold buffet. As we have a baby we also ate a couple of nights in the hotel. Don't expect culinary expertise but if you desperately need convenience like us with baby and a bedtime routine ham and eggs was sufficient !!Location very convenient at the top of La Ramblas and near Placa La Catalunya and Bus turistic routes. Our room was at the back of the hotel and we did not have noise from the very busy street at the front. Ok as we did not need an interesting view - we actually kept the curtains closed the whole time. The floor covering in the hall outside our room was marble and footsteps heard a lot and voices echoed from the lift lobby. The walls do not seem to be very sound resistant and are more partition than solid wall. Constant snoring throughout the whole night was endured by us from another room. Not sure if from room above, below, or to either side. Sound-proofing therefore not great. A great location for a hotel that also provides more than basic accommodation and attention. Enjoy. 
