<Author>maidmarian
<Content>good 3starwith a great location I booked this hotel through Flying Visits for a 3 night stay in Nov'05 and I must say I will definitly go through a travel agent from now. The level of service and expertise I had while dealing with them was so reassuring. I knew they would take good care of me if I had any problems and as they have actually seen a lot of the hotels they sell at least I know I will not end up in a dump.Anyway, the Lleo hotel is in a great location just off Plaza Catalunya and Las Ramblas. There is a cash machine directly outside the hotel on the left and a shop just a few doors up where you can buy your disposable camera or films!! If you walk back up towards the Plaza Catalunya you will pass a number of little shops, and a Starbucks across the street and within 3 minutes you will come to the start of Las Ramblas. There is a metro/train station at Plaza Catalunya, just outside the coffee shop Caf茅 Zurich, which will take you anywhere you want to go. You can also catch the Bus Turistico from the Plaza Catalunya. If you go right when you come out of the Lleo Hotel for about a 100yards, you will come to a small bar where you can dine or have a late drink. This is great as the hotel bar closes at 11.30pm. All the air-conditioned rooms are very comfortable with fridge, safe, piped music and hair-dryer but BBC News and Sky News are the only english speaking channels. Some rooms are quiet small. In ours the bathtub was just right for me (but then i am only 5foot tall!!), and the dressing table was right up against the bed but as we were only sleeping there we didnt find it a problem. There is a small bar with a lounge area and the buffet breakfast is served in a room beside the lounge area until 12:00 every day. There is a snack bar and also a non-smoking dining hall beside the breakfast room. There is a vending machine in the lobby, just in front of the elevator, where you can get water, soft drinks and even cans of beer!! The lobby also has a lot of information on sightseeing and the reception staff are very helpful if you need directions. Just behind the elevator is the piano room and a business centre where you can check your emails. All in all a great stay in Barcelona.Directions: Take the Airport bus from outside Terminal A and get off at the Plaza Catalunya Stop (journey time approx 20mins and the cost is approx Eur 3.95 per person). You will be dropped off on the far side of the Plaza Catalunya. The hotel is only a 5 minutes walk away so cross over towards the fountain to the other side of Plaza Cataluna, walk around the coffee shop (Caf茅 Zurich) and down the Carrer de Pelai, cross over at Starbucks coffee shop and keep walking down the street away from Plaza Catalunya. You will see the Lleo hotel on your left. 
